		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Michael Copperman</span></strong>&rsquo;s writing has appeared in <em>Oxford American</em>, <em>Creative Nonfiction</em>, and <em>Guernica</em>. He lives in Eugene, Oregon, and is the recipient of a fellowship from the Oregon Arts Council. From 2002 to 2004 he taught fourth grade in the rural public schools of the Mississippi Delta, and he is currently seeking representation for a novel about that experience.</p><a href="/contributors/michael-copperman" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
